      <span class="faq-q-text">Which structured data format should I use for AI search?</span>
      <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
    </button>
    <div class="faq-a" id="which-structured-data-format-should-i-use-for-ai-s"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>JSON-LD. Every major AI search engine. Google, Bing, Perplexity, ChatGPT. Processes JSON-LD. Google explicitly recommends it. Place JSON-LD in a <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag in your HTML <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> section and render it server-side.</p></div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="faq-item">
    <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="how-many-schema-types-should-i-add-to-one-page">
